      "text": "Last edit about 3 years ago by svayambhu108\n\n186\n-3 6) It is somehow God + yet is not; some‐ how Christ + yet is not. 7) It knows all things. surely someone in the world who knows about the Holy Spirit will recognize that This is what \"Valis\" is about (but the humble author did not). Look at their stance at the end; it is that of the eleven at the time of Acts - in fact \"Valis\" is a retelling of the story of the spirit of the risen Lord returning to the grieving disciples; Horselover Fat's grief",
